 conceptions of time as chronological.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aOntology in literature. 0aOther (Philosophy) in literature. 0aOther minds (Theory of knowledge) in literature. 0aSpace and time in literature. 0aTime in literature. 4aShakespeare 2018. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aProust.  aShakespeare.  aanachronicity.  aanachronism.  aheterogeneity.  alove.  apost-Nietzschean theory.  aspace.  atime.  atrauma.1 aTambling, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779351540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847793515423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847793515/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles